cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software or the research notes it contains, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "QuantumOS: a sensitivity-instrument simulator for constraint-first quantum operating system design"
authors:
  - family-names: Mason
    given-names: Tony
    email: fsgeek@cs.ubc.ca
    affiliation: "University of British Columbia"
abstract: >-
  A Python discrete-event simulator for exploring operating-system resource
  management in an entanglement-first quantum computer. The simulator is a
  sensitivity instrument, not a point predictor: it tests whether proposed OS
  abstractions (entanglement leases, syndrome rounds, decoder capacity, switch
  paths, calibration epochs) deserve to exist, under the admission rule that no
  quantity enters the object model without naming the decision that reads it.
  The repository includes the simulator, its test suite, pre-registered
  experiment batteries with OpenTimestamps-anchored falsification records, and
  the research notes the instrument forced. The work is produced through a
  documented human-AI collaborative method: research direction, vetoes, and
  claims discipline by the author; exploration, implementation, and analysis
  conducted in extended collaboration with Anthropic Claude model instances,
  as recorded throughout the repository's specs and commit history.
license: MIT
doi: 10.5281/zenodo.21340726
repository-code: "https://github.com/fsgeek/quantumos"
version: 0.1.0
date-released: 2026-07-13
keywords:
